  "No, because trace is not a linear function": "",
  "The zero matrix has trace 0. If tr(A) = 0 and tr(B) = 0, then tr(A+B) = tr(A) + tr(B) = 0. If tr(A) = 0, then tr(cA) = c*tr(A) = 0. All three subspace conditions are met.": "",
  "Consider the subset S = {(x, y) in R^2 : xy >= 0}. Is S a subspace of R^2?": "",
