  "No, because some months might have negative anomalies": "",
  "No, because the zero vector has all zeros, not realistic temperatures": "",
  "The condition x1 + x2 + ... + x12 = 0 is a homogeneous linear equation. The solution set of any homogeneous linear equation (or system of such equations) is always a subspace. The zero vector satisfies it, and the constraint is preserved under addition and scalar multiplication.": "",
  "A data scientist works with the space of all 3x3 matrices. She considers the set of upper triangular matrices (entries below the diagonal are zero). Is this a subspace?": "",
  "No, because the identity matrix is upper triangular but not the zero matrix": "",
